KOMPOT USER MANUAL: EMULATION

Emulation is provided by QEMU. A disk utility can be invoked with
"qemu-img" to create storage image devices. "qemu-system-x86-64"
is used with the following options to start QEMU.

OPTIONS:

-enable-kvm			: Enable KVM support.

-cpu <host/x64_86>	: Sets CPU architecture.

-smp <n>			: Allocate n cores.

-vga <card>			: Set graphics card. "cirrus" for windows.
					: Suggested: "virtio" Other: "sdl", "cirrus"

-display <opt>		: Set display options.
				    : Suggested: "gtk,gl=on"

-cdrom <iso image>	: Loads installation media into virtual cdrom.

-boot menu=on		: Enable boot menu.

-drive <hdd image>	: Sets virtual storage media.

-m 8G				: Set memory.

-name "<name>"		: Set name of VM.

-show-cursor		: Enables cursor.
